measure.CatchLine: Allows counties to partition and rezone up to 200 acres of lands within Eastern Oregon Border Economic Development Region from exclusive farm use to residential uses.
measure.MeasureSummary:
Allows counties to partition and rezone up to 200 acres of lands within Eastern Oregon Border Economic Development Region from exclusive farm use to residential uses. 
	Takes effect on 91st day following adjournment sine die.
measure.RelatingToFull: Relating to Eastern Oregon Border Economic Development Region housing; and prescribing an effective date.
measure.RelatingTo: Relating to Eastern Oregon Border Economic Development Region housing; and prescribing an effective date.

historyActions.ActionText: Introduction and first reading. Referred to President's desk.
Third reading.  Carried by Findley.  Passed.
historyActions.VoteText: Ayes, 16; Nays, 12--Burdick, Dembrow, Gelser, Gorsek, Heard, Jama, Lieber, Prozanski, Riley, Taylor, Thatcher, Wagner; Excused, 2--Manning Jr, Thomsen.

historyActions.ActionText: First reading. Referred to Speaker's desk.
Third reading. Carried by Owens. Passed.
historyActions.VoteText: Ayes, 32; Nays, 27--Campos, Clem, Dexter, Fahey, Gomberg, Grayber, Holvey, Hudson, Kropf, Marsh, McLain, Nathanson, Neron, Nosse, Pham, Power, Prusak, Rayfield, Ruiz, Salinas, Sanchez, Schouten, Sollman, Valderrama, Wilde, Williams, Witt.
